<h2>List of papers (3)</h2>
<ul>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2010/index.html">SLE 2010</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2010/paper12.html">Canonical Method Names for Java: Using Implementation Semantics to Identify Synonymous Verbs</a></em> (<a href="../profile/EinarWHøst.html">Einar W. Høst</a>, <a href="../profile/BjarteMØstvold.html">Bjarte M. Østvold</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t5b.html"><span class="tagM" title=" The contribution is a language-oriented analysis of code to infer canonical method names from implementation semantics.
">T5B</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t6g.html"><span class="tagL" title=" It targets developer-facing naming conventions and their cognitive/communication aspects in code bases.
">T6G</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t5e.html"><span class="tagL" title=" The approach is validated empirically by mining/analyzing Java code and assessing synonym detection.
">T5E</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2012/index.html">SLE 2012</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2012/keynote2.html">Addressing Cognitive and Social Challenges in Designing and Using Ontologies in the Biomedical Domain</a></em> (<a href="../profile/MargaretAnneStorey.html">Margaret-Anne Storey</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t3e.html"><span class="tagM" title=" The paper’s main topic is the design and use of ontologies, focusing on practical challenges in ontology work.
">T3E</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagL" title=" The core issues discussed are cognitive and human factors (understandability, collaboration) affecting ontology use.
">T5H</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t6g.html"><span class="tagL" title=" It explicitly frames ontology engineering as a socio-technical activity involving social processes and coordination.
">T6G</span></a></li><li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2024/index.html">SLE 2024</a>)</span> <em><a href="../sle2024/paper19.html">AI Effects on Research and Education: A Programming and Software Language Perspective (Panel)</a></em> (<a href="../profile/RalfLämmel.html">Ralf Lämmel</a>) 
<a href="../tag/t6g.html"><span class="tagM" title=" The panel centers on socio-technical impacts of LLMs on research, education, and programming practice.
">T6G</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t4g.html"><span class="tagL" title=" It explicitly discusses large language models as a disruptive technology relevant to AI-for-SLE and tooling.
">T4G</span></a>
<a href="../tag/t6d.html"><span class="tagL" title=" The discussion connects perspectives across communities (PL, compilers, education) to identify shared challenges.
">T6D</span></a></li></ul>
